“我们疯狂地吃家乡菜，因为没有冰箱”。
"We ate our hometown food crazily because there was no fridge."
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
查琼芳 第一批上海支援湖北医疗队队员、上海交大医学院附属仁济医院呼吸科主治医师3月6日，支援湖北第四十二天，武汉，阴天。
Chao Qiongfang was the first member of the Shanghai Support Hubei Medical Team. He was a respiratory doctor attached to Yan Chai Hospital of Shanghai Jiao University Medical School.
今天的天阴沉沉的，可是吃到家乡菜的我们心里却是乐开了花。
Today, the sky is overcast, but we eat the home dishes in our hearts is happy to bloom.
我们从昨晚开始疯狂地品尝平时即使在上海也少有机会吃到的锦江大厨做的美食，更何况是带着满满爱心的大菜。
Since last night, we have been savoring the delicious food made by the chef of Jinjiang, which is rare even in Shanghai, not to mention the delicious food filled with love.
说疯狂是有原因的，这些食物都有一定的保质期，两天、三天，最长的XO酱常温也就六天。
There's a reason for craziness. These foods all have a shelf life, two days, three days, and the longest one is six days.
本着不能辜负爱心，不能浪费粮食的原则，在没有冰箱保存的前提下，最好的办法就是进自己的肚子！伙伴们会带着自己的那份进餐厅，也会想办法拿个塑料袋挂在窗口，只为可以多放几天，当然更多的则是埋头大吃啦。
Under the principle of not letting go of love and wasting food, the best thing to do without a refrigerator is to go inside! The guys will take their share into the restaurant and try to hang a plastic bag at the window just for a few more days, and more often than not, too much.
家乡送来的美食都有一定的保质期，在没有冰箱的情况下，开封后需要在短时间内吃完。
Gourmet food from home has a certain shelf life, in the absence of refrigerators, Kaifeng after the need to eat in a short time.
本文图片 查琼芳 提供群里老师那份什么东西吃到哪天的善意提醒，让大家更有了紧迫感。
In this picture, Cha Qiongfang offers a kind reminder of what the teacher in the group ate until which day, giving us a sense of urgency.
哈哈，这也是“甜蜜的负担”啊！吃完八宝辣酱和蟹粉就着白粥的奢侈早餐后，继续酒店门口消食活动。
Ha ha, this is also "sweet burden" ah! After eating Baobao hot sauce and crab powder with porridge luxurious breakfast, continue the hotel door eating activities.
这次我和周医生走的稍微远了一点，来到了马路的对面。
This time I and Dr. Zhou walked a little further, came across the road.
同样的商场大门都是紧闭的，肯德基、屈臣氏、儿童乐园都是大门紧闭。
The same mall doors are closed, KFC, Tucson's, Children's Park are closed.
唯一开着的就是一家酒店的门，在酒店的门口，我们看到了沪牌的车子，仔细一看，原来是上海东方医院的国家紧急医学救援队的车子。
The only open door is a hotel, in front of the hotel, we saw Shanghai-brand cars, a closer look, it was the Shanghai Oriental Hospital of the National Emergency Medical Rescue Team's car.
酒店门口停放的东方医院国家紧急医学救援队车辆。
Orient Hospital National Emergency Medical Rescue Team vehicle parked in front of the hotel.
人生何处不相逢啊！东方医院工作的武汉客厅就在我们之前住的万豪酒店边上，在金银潭医院马路对面，现在我们搬了家，没想到还是邻居啊。
Where is the life? The living room of Dongfang Hospital is next to the Marriott Hotel where we used to live, across the street from the Golden Pool Hospital.
现在，远离家乡，看到上海的车子都让我觉得亲切起来了。
Now, far from my hometown, I feel kind to see the cars in Shanghai.
中午依旧带着家乡菜进入餐厅，今天的餐厅为大家准备了“武昌鱼”。
At noon is still taking home food into the restaurant, today's restaurant for everyone prepared "Wuchang fish."
吃完午饭，我们又喝了酒店陈经理特意为大家准备的银耳桃胶羹。
After lunch, we drank the hotel manager Chen specially prepared for everyone's silver ear peach soup.
昨天我们刚刚喝了暖胃的红糖姜茶，看样子陈经理准备把我们“宠坏”啊。
Yesterday we had a warm stomach of brown sugar ginger tea, it seems that manager Chen is ready to "spoil" us.
今天夜班，下午我美美地睡了一觉，睡醒后跟家里视频了一下，又是叮嘱多喝水、多休息、多吃水果、多吃饭。
Tonight night shift, afternoon I fell asleep, wake up with a video at home, is to order more water, more rest, more fruit, eat more food.
这么多的爱心，我能不吃吗？上班前，我收到来自仁济医院在雷神山的后勤施阳老师的问候，说今晚会给我们在金银潭医院的四人小分队送来仁济的娘家菜，同样也是家乡的味道，是我们仁济食堂沈大成做的真空包装的美食，有四喜烤麸、有油焖笋......今天的白天，在家乡的美食中度过了，感谢每一份美食的制作者。
Before I went to work, I received greetings from Shi Yang, a logistics teacher from Yan Chai Hospital in Lei Sheng Shan, saying that the four-person team from Yinji Hospital would be served to our four-member team this evening. It was also a home-cooked meal made by Shen Dacheng of our Yenji Cafeteria.
晚上，带着吃撑的肚子将继续三女将夜值。
In the evening, will continue to carry the three women with the stomach will be worth night.
希望每一个病人都平平安安的，希望夜无殊。
I hope every patient is safe, and I hope the night is special.
（澎湃新闻记者 陈斯斯 整理）本期编辑邢潭推荐阅读。
(Peng Pai journalist Chen Si: This issue editor Xing Tam recommends reading.
